
[1]appurtenant

   APPUR'TENANT, a.

   1. Belonging to; pertaining to of right.

   2. In law, common appurtenant is that which is annexed to land, and can
   be claimed only by prescription or immemorial usage, or a legal
   presumption of a special grant.
